ğŸ“‚ upload_fs.py â€” Upload Files to LittleFS

If your project uses LittleFS for storing configuration files, app data, etc., you need a way to upload those files to the ESP32â€™s flash memory.

PlatformIO doesnâ€™t upload the data/ folder by default unless explicitly configured. This is where upload_fs.py comes in.
ğŸ“„ File: upload_fs.py

# upload_fs.py
Import("env")
env.Replace(FS="LittleFS", FSTYPE="littlefs")

ğŸ’¡ What this does:

    Tells PlatformIO to use LittleFS (instead of default SPIFFS)

    Sets the correct filesystem type and flags

    Ensures pio run --target uploadfs uploads files to flash in the spiffs partition


